servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil.

Place packet of @pesto{1/2%cup} in a #cup{} of warm water to bring to room temperature.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @ground turkey{10%oz}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, half the
@panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, half the @garlic powder{1%tsp}, half the @Italian seasoning{1/2%tbsp}, 
2 TBSP water, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and @pepper{}. Form into 10-12 1 1/2-inch meatballs.

> Swap in turkey for beef.

Place meatballs on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Roast on top rack until browned and cooked
through, ~{14-16%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%oz} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al
dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain, then return to pot.

Toss with 2 TBSP @butter{2%tbsp} and a pinch of salt and pepper.

> TIP: If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get
> started on them now!

While pasta cooks, melt 1 TBSP @butter{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{}, preferably #nonstick{},
over medium heat. Add remaining @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and cook, stirring, until golden
brown, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Transfer to a #small bowl{}; season with salt and pepper. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for panko over medium-high heat. Add
@crushed tomatoes{1}(can), remaining @garlic powder{1%tsp}, remaining @Italian seasoning{1/2%tbsp},
@sugar{1/4%tsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce is warmed
through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Serve spaghetti, meatballs, toasted panko, red sauce, pesto, @balsamic glaze{5%tsp},
@Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp}, and @?chili flakes{} family style and let everyone build their own
plates.

> Don't forget to serve with any extra items you may have ordered to build out your meal!

> Ground poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.